<div1 type="trialAccount" id="t17680907-12">
               <interp inst="t17680907-12" type="collection" value="BAILEY"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17680907-12" type="year" value="1768"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17680907-12" type="uri" value="sessionsPapers/17680907"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17680907-12" type="date" value="17680907"></interp>
               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t17680907-12-off60-c118" targOrder="Y" targets="t17680907-12-defend144 t17680907-12-off60 t17680907-12-verdict64"></join>
         
               <p>510. (L) 
               
                  <persName id="t17680907-12-defend144" type="defendantName">
                     John 
                     Foster 
                  <interp inst="t17680907-12-defend144" type="surname" value="Foster"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17680907-12-defend144" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17680907-12-defend144" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
             was indicted for <rs id="t17680907-12-off60" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17680907-12-off60" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17680907-12-off60" type="offenceSubcategory" value="grandLarceny"></interp>
               stealing a silver pint mug, value 39 s.
            </rs> the property of 
               
                  <persName id="t17680907-12-victim146" type="victimName">
                     Andrew 
                     Christie 
                  <interp inst="t17680907-12-victim146" type="surname" value="Christie"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17680907-12-victim146" type="given" value="Andrew"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17680907-12-victim146" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t17680907-12-off60 t17680907-12-victim146"></join>
                  </persName>
                
            , <rs id="t17680907-12-cd61" type="crimeDate">Aug. 10</rs>
                  <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t17680907-12-off60 t17680907-12-cd61"></join> ++</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17680907-12-person147">
                  Andrew 
                  Christie 
               <interp inst="t17680907-12-person147" type="surname" value="Christie"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17680907-12-person147" type="given" value="Andrew"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17680907-12-person147" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . <rs id="t17680907-12-viclabel62" type="occupation">I keep the Red Cow, a public-house</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17680907-12-victim146 t17680907-12-viclabel62"></join> in <placeName id="t17680907-12-crimeloc63">Long lane</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t17680907-12-crimeloc63" type="placeName" value="Long lane"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17680907-12-crimeloc63" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17680907-12-off60 t17680907-12-crimeloc63"></join>; I was out of town on the 10th of August, I came home the next day; then the prisoner was in Wood-street Compter.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17680907-12-person148">
                  Thomas 
                  Rowland 
               <interp inst="t17680907-12-person148" type="surname" value="Rowland"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17680907-12-person148" type="given" value="Thomas"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17680907-12-person148" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I frequently have a pint of beer at Mr. Christie's house after dinner; I and Mr. Hill, a carpenter in Jewin street, were there drinking together, he had a silver pint, and I a pewter one; the prisoner came in, and sat close by Mr. Hill; we asked him what trade he was; he said, something like that of a shipwright, we did not like his look; Mr. Hill having an occasion to go backwards, whispered me to have an eye to his silver mug; the prisoner got close to it, and whipped<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="176809070009"></xptr> it into his left-hand coat pocket, and was getting out of the box; I got round, and took hold of him, and said, young man, you have got a mug in your pocket, I saw the beer shine in it; he took it out himself; I called the people, and he was taken to the Compter.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17680907-12-person149">
                  John 
                  Corbet 
               <interp inst="t17680907-12-person149" type="surname" value="Corbet"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17680907-12-person149" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17680907-12-person149" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am constable, this mug was delivered into my charge with the prisoner (produced and deposed to by prosecutor.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's defence.</p>
               <p>I went into that house, and into the necessary, and when I came in again I got hold of the wrong mug, but I never went out of the house with it.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17680907-12-verdict64" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17680907-12-verdict64" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               Guilty
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17680907-12-punish65" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17680907-12-punish65" type="punishmentCategory" value="noPunish"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17680907-12-punish65" type="punishmentSubcategory" value="sentenceRespited"></interp>
                     <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y" targets="t17680907-12-defend144 t17680907-12-punish65"></join>
               
                     <note>[No punishment. See summary.]</note>
               
                  </rs>
               </p>
            </div1>
